Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100029796845697></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100029796845697><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>How to be a Successful Rogue</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=96009><span id= >Pikkit</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 12th 8:32 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When you are a Rogue it is important to try to sell often becuase you can get encumbered easily(Unless Your a Barbairian or Dwarf). Try to mooch a Sow whenever you can. Hit /druid and see who over Lv 13 is in the zone and send them a tell. Or hit /Shaman and see if there are any Lv 9s. It often works well to kiss up till you are blue in the face. Tell how strong they are etc.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Half Elves should start at Kelethin, or Quenos. Kelethin has a good Lv 10 area. Crush Bone. And so does Quenos. Black Burrow. <br>     Dark Elves...you are a hard race to play. Stay near Newbie Log until you are strong enough to take Lv 4-6 stuff near the Ent to EC. Then you can venture into Ec when your around Lv 7.<br>     When you first start try to get mostly leather armor. Dont bother getting leather Belts and wrists and stuff like that. Heres the important stuff, SAVE YOUR MONEY. I havent bought water for 5 Lvs now. Water is for restoring you mana. Buy Banded Tunics Pants and Helm.<br>     At Lv 8 I think, I'm not sure what Lv, You will get safe fall. It is extremely useful. Try jumping off small things at first then get a Cleric or Druid to follow you around when you fall half way from the elevator. Then all the way from the top. Then the Wizard spires (BE VERY CAREFUL) after jumping off from the bank in Kelethin only causes around 60 Damage.<br>     You will get Pick Pocket at Lv 7. It sounds liuke you'll get bukoos of cash from this skill, but you wont unless the thing you are stealing from has money on them. Dont try the Banker.<br>     Hide and Sneak will save your life more times than you can imagine. When you just walking along to where ever it is your going, Stop, Hide, Sneak,Unclick Sneak if it worked, And keep going until the skill regenerates. DO NOT HIDE ON BOATS. Your probably thinking " Theres nothing wrong with hiding on boats!" But your wrong. WQHen you zone and your hidden, the game shuts down and you go to your desktop. One of two things will happen, You will log back on and be at the border of the zone you just came into and you will proably be able to see land, or you will stay on the boat and miss your stop.<br>     Next is a Rogues pride and joy. Backstab! This skill will take a lot of time to master but it's worth it. If you have extra time on your hands go to the Newbie area and Backstab lower Lv stuff. You must have a Piercing Weapon in one of your hands for it to work. And you have to be facing thier back, Duh.<br>     When you gt Dual Wield Sell your shield and put your fastest weapon in the Primary Slot. Try to practice with a 1hs weapon so you can have a quick one and a strong one.<br>     Dwarfs shoudl go to Kelethin newbie area, Same with Gnomes.<br>     Halflings should jump off a Bridge. They do not have a good mid Lv area. And they have Fuzzy Feet. <br>     Rogues can solo small non mab critters but the going is slower than Christmas(BTW if you think my Posting is good send me a Game Cube, Lol) it is much better if rouges group. But seeing as rogues are not as strong as warriors my not always get a group together.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
