<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100035711359279></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100035711359279><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100035711359279>RE: How to be a Successful Rogue</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100035711359279#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>224 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 13th 12:58 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nice post. A couple comments: You get safe fall at level 12, not 8. BTW, when you get to level 18 or 19 and you're wondering why your safe fall isn't improving, it's because rogues get a hard cap of 94 in the safe fall skill. This is reached (assuming you keep it maxed) at lvl 18. I'm not quite sure if the hiding on a boat bug is common, but I've never experienced. I practice hide and sneak all the time on those boring boat trips and I've never been kicked off when the boat zoned while I was hidden. It might just something with your system that doesn't like you very much. A tip about practicing your hide, backstab, and pickpocket skills all at the same time (and using them effectively as well). Right click on one of your blank squares in the socials menu, and type the following:<br>/attack off<br>/doability &lt;# of your hide ability slot&gt;<br>/doability &lt;# of your backstab slot&gt;<br>/doability &lt;# of your pickpocket slot&gt;<br>/attack on<br><br>This is specifically made for fighting in a group with a tank (hopefully not you). I use /attack on and off instead of simply /a because /a does a toggle; there are times when you want to backstab before attacking, and times when you want to backstab while attacking. Hiding during battle has the effect of evading; it lowers the mob's aggro on you. With a good skill in hide, it will likely turn the mob away from you and back on the tank, if it was even on you in the first place. After the mob turns, you get a backstab in and pick its pockets (A true rogue will always pickpocket the mobs in his group; just be careful you're not fighting a mob like a dervish cutthroat, who will anounce out loud your attempts to steal from it). Finally it turns attack back on. As long as you don't have a haste effect, the hide, pickpocket, and backstab buttons will all pop up again at the same time. With a haste the backstab will regenerate faster then the others; don't wait for hide and pickpocket to become available if the mob's back is towards you and you have a chance to backstab. I have been using this tactic as long as I've had backstab and it has helped greatly to keep my hide, pickpocket, and backstab skills up. One last comment: Don't jump off a bridge, halflings! You are a great rogue race (though not as good as barbies and dorfs). Whatever race you are, you can always find comfort in the fact that you don't suck as much as the dark elf. But you are a dark elf, you say? Well you might as well transfer your stuff to another character and destroy that one immediately! J/K; but seriously, dark elf rogues are a challenging combo to play, and not just because they are an evil race. They have the worst starting stats of any rogue race (don't say a word about there are tons of strength items out there or crap like that, I'm talking what you start with. Like Tallicus has said many times, you take your strength items to buff your strength up to what a dorf or barbie started at, and that barbie or dorf will take dexterity and agility items to put some major shame in the dark elf's face.)<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 28th Dwarf Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
